WEBVTT

NOTE Captions for "Pollis's three logs, and what each one prevents" (Topic 9).
NOTE No audio track yet by decision; these captions carry the narration. Source
NOTE of truth: learn/manim/scripts/three-logs.md

00:00.000 --> 00:20.000
Three logs. One signing key. One address: verify dot pollis dot com. Each one closes a different attack.

00:20.000 --> 00:40.000
The first holds every identity key we've ever published. To hand you the wrong key, we'd have to write the fake key here, permanently, in public, where the real owner's own app is looking.

00:40.000 --> 01:00.000
And the rule on this log is that versions only move forward. We can't slip an old key back in, or renumber history.

01:00.000 --> 01:15.000
The second holds every commit in every conversation. Groups move forward in epochs, and everyone has to apply them in the same order.

01:15.000 --> 01:32.000
So watch what a dishonest server would try: two different commits, both claiming to be epoch eight. The group splits, half in one reality, half in another.

01:32.000 --> 01:45.000
The log's rule makes that impossible. One epoch, one commit. And look at what's stored, it's sealed. The log publishes the order of a conversation, never a word of its content.

01:45.000 --> 02:10.000
The third holds the fingerprint of every app we've released. Build a special version for one person and that fingerprint is either in this public log, where anyone can see it, or missing from it, where that person's own app notices. There's no third option.

02:10.000 --> 02:25.000
Why three logs instead of one? Because a signed head for one must never work as a head for another.

02:25.000 --> 02:40.000
Take a valid head from the commit log and try to pass it off as one for the binaries log. It doesn't fit. Each tree signs under its own context, so the signature says which tree it belongs to.

02:40.000 --> 02:52.000
And the limits, plainly. These don't make us honest, they make lying undeniable rather than impossible. They also say nothing about bugs. A log proves what we published, not that it's correct.

02:52.000 --> 03:00.000
One practical note. The logs rebuild once a day, so something published an hour ago may genuinely not be in there yet. That's why your app says "pending" instead of raising an alarm.
